# Paired Benchmark

This folder contains the scripts and output files for the fully paired PBMC RNA-ATAC integration benchmark.

In the paired setting, each cell has both RNA and ATAC measurements. This setting was used to compare the integration performance of MultiVI, GLUE and MOFA+ under complete multi-omics data availability.

## Folder structure

```text
PAIRED_benchmark/
├── paired_GLUE/
│   ├── PAIRED_run_glue.py
│   ├── glue_latent.csv
│   └── glue_latent.h5ad
│
├── paired_MOFA/
│   ├── PAIRED_run_mofa.py
│   ├── mofa_latent.csv
│   └── mofa_latent.h5ad
│
├── paired_MULTIVI/
│   ├── PAIRED_run_MultiVI.py
│   ├── multivi_full_latent.csv
│   ├── multivi_full_latent.h5ad
│   └── multivi_full_latent_annotated_final.h5ad
│
├── generate_paired_figures.py
├── run_paired_benchmark.py
├── strict_paired_benchmark_metrics.csv
├── strict_paired_celltypewise_knn.csv
├── paired_ari_summary.csv
├── paired_immune_programme_smoothness_metrics.csv
└── paired_immune_programme_smoothness_by_programme.csv
```

## Method folders

### `paired_MULTIVI/`

Contains the script and outputs for running MultiVI on the paired dataset.

Main files:

```text
PAIRED_run_MultiVI.py
multivi_full_latent.csv
multivi_full_latent.h5ad
multivi_full_latent_annotated_final.h5ad
```

### `paired_GLUE/`

Contains the script and outputs for running GLUE on the paired dataset.

Main files:

```text
PAIRED_run_glue.py
glue_latent.csv
glue_latent.h5ad
```

### `paired_MOFA/`

Contains the script and outputs for running MOFA+ on the paired dataset.

Main files:

```text
PAIRED_run_mofa.py
mofa_latent.csv
mofa_latent.h5ad
```

## Script-output summary

| Script | Main outputs |
|---|---|
| `paired_MULTIVI/PAIRED_run_MultiVI.py` | `multivi_full_latent.csv`, `multivi_full_latent.h5ad`, `multivi_full_latent_annotated_final.h5ad` |
| `paired_GLUE/PAIRED_run_glue.py` | `glue_latent.csv`, `glue_latent.h5ad` |
| `paired_MOFA/PAIRED_run_mofa.py` | `mofa_latent.csv`, `mofa_latent.h5ad` |
| `run_paired_benchmark.py` | `strict_paired_benchmark_metrics.csv`, `strict_paired_celltypewise_knn.csv`, immune programme smoothness CSV files |
| `generate_paired_figures.py` | Paired UMAPs and benchmark figures |

## Benchmark outputs

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `strict_paired_benchmark_metrics.csv` | Main paired benchmark metrics for MultiVI, GLUE and MOFA+ |
| `strict_paired_celltypewise_knn.csv` | Cell-type-wise KNN purity results |
| `paired_ari_summary.csv` | Supplementary ARI clustering-agreement results |
| `paired_immune_programme_smoothness_metrics.csv` | Overall immune programme smoothness results |
| `paired_immune_programme_smoothness_by_programme.csv` | Immune programme smoothness results separated by programme |

## Metrics

The paired benchmark mainly used:

- NMI
- Balanced silhouette score
- Balanced KNN purity
- ARI
- Immune programme smoothness

The main report focused on NMI, balanced silhouette score and balanced KNN purity as the primary cell-type conservation metrics.

## Notes

- The same marker-based PBMC cell-type annotation was used across all methods.
- Leiden clusters were generated separately for each method.
- UMAPs are used for visualization and should not be compared only by shape.
- The paired benchmark was used as the complete-data baseline before the r75 missing-modality benchmark.
